   5 import contextlib

   7 from pip_shims import Wheel
   8 
   9 
  10 def _wheel_supported(self, tags=None):
  11     # Ignore current platform. Support everything.
  12     return True
  13 
  14 
  15 def _wheel_support_index_min(self, tags=None):
  16     # All wheels are equal priority for sorting.
  17     return 0
  18 
  19 
  20 @contextlib.contextmanager
  21 def _allow_all_wheels():
  22     """Monkey patch pip.Wheel to allow all wheels
  23 
  24     The usual checks against platforms and Python versions are ignored to allow
  25     fetching all available entries in PyPI. This also saves the candidate cache
  26     and set a new one, or else the results from the previous non-patched calls
  27     will interfere.
  28     """
  29     original_wheel_supported = Wheel.supported
  30     original_support_index_min = Wheel.support_index_min
  31 
  32     Wheel.supported = _wheel_supported
  33     Wheel.support_index_min = _wheel_support_index_min
  34     yield
  35     Wheel.supported = original_wheel_supported
  36     Wheel.support_index_min = original_support_index_min
  37 
  38 
  39 def get_hashes(cache, req):
  40     if req.is_vcs:
  41         return set()
  42 
  43     ireq = req.as_ireq()
  44 
  45     if ireq.editable:
  46         return set()
  47 
  48     if req.is_file_or_url:
  49         # TODO: Get the hash of the linked artifact?
  50         return set()
  51 
  52     if not ireq.is_pinned:
  53         return set()
  54 
  55     with _allow_all_wheels():
  56         matching_candidates = req.find_all_matches()
  57 
  58     return {
  59         cache.get_hash(candidate.location)
  60         for candidate in matching_candidates
  61     }
